Re: Learn Japanese through MANGA
by Hyperworm » Sat 04.30.2011 8:28 pm Wow, it's pretty impressive that a legal free website like Jコミ exists at all. Of course, the selection isn't very big. It's surprising to see Love Hina being offered ._.becki_kanou's advice is very good. You don't want to attempt to learn basic grammar through manga. Use manga at the stage when you already know a good deal of grammar, and just want to pick up vocab and make yourself more familiar with slang.I prefer reading manga from tankoubon rather than online. I'd advocate buying a couple from yesasia/jbox (or Japanese sites like bk1 or HMV) if you already know which series you like. (Get the feeling I've left out a site there...)
